==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Falseness
<hw>False"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of being false;
contrariety to the fact; inaccuracy; want of integrity or uprightness;
double dealing; unfaithfulness; treachery; perfidy; <as>as, the
<ex>falseness</ex> of a report, a drawing, or a singer's notes; the
<ex>falseness</ex> of a man, or of his word.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Falser</ent>⟦br⟧
